    %% Core Neurobiological Substrates
    Neurobiological Substrates of Consciousness
      Central Role of Thalamocortical System
        ::icon(fa fa-brain)
        Evidence: Thalamus has a "central topological role"
        Operates via reciprocal corticothalamocortical loops
        Core vs. matrix thalamic neurons regulate content (e.g., perceptual constancy) and state
      Critical Neuromodulatory Systems (ACh, NE, DA, 5-HT)
        ::icon(fa fa-sliders-h)
        Evidence: Originate in brainstem/midbrain/basal forebrain
        Project broadly to modulate synaptic transmission & global brain states
        Enable flexible transitions (e.g., sleep-wake) via "flip-flop" switch models
      Specific Regulatory Nuclei & Circuits
        Thalamic Reticular Nucleus (TRN)
          Regulates thalamocortical dynamics; ACh induces burst firing
        Locus Coeruleus (LC)
          Vertebrate-specific noradrenergic hub with conserved, widespread projections
    
